            'i.harmful.h2': 'Harmful Habits',
            'i.harmful.sub': 'Three things we don\'t talk about openly enough',
            'i.h3.h3': '🎰 Gambling — the addiction that has no smell and can\'t be seen',
            'i.h3.body': '<p>Gambling is the only addiction where the brain responds <strong>identical to cocaine</strong> in terms of the dopamine spike. It\'s not a matter of weak will—it\'s a clinically recognized behavioral addiction.</p> <p class="mt-8">Online betting, sports bonuses and casino apps are designed by behavioral psychologists with one goal in mind:<strong>to bring you back</strong>. Every "near win" is programmed. Every free turn is a lure.</p> <div class="research"> <strong>Bulgarian Academy of Sciences / OFFNews, 2024</strong><br/>Between 4% and 7% of Bulgarian adults suffer from gambling addiction — double the global average. 12% of high school students in Bulgaria are problem gamblers. Over 54,000 have officially registered as gambling addicts (Eurocom / Novinite, end of 2025) — and the real number is many times higher, as most people do not admit the problem even to themselves.</div> <div class="research"> <strong>Lancet Psychiatry, 2023</strong><br/>Brain scans show that in people with gambling addiction, the prefrontal cortex (responsible for controlling impulses) is structurally damaged—the same as with long-term alcohol use.</div> <table class="food-table mt-16"> <thead><tr><th>Flag</th><th>Reality</th></tr></thead> <tbody> <tr><td>"I\'ll get my money back"</td><td><em class="red">Medium: A problem gambler loses more when trying to recoup losses</em></td></tr> <tr><td>"I have a system"</td><td><em class="red">The casino is mathematically designed - there is no</em></td></tr> <tr><td>winning system "Just for fun"</td><td><em class="amber">Free bets lead to paid - intentionally</em></td></tr> <tr><td>Stop</td><td><em class="green">Cognitive behavioral therapy has a 60–80% success rate</em></td></tr> </tbody> </table> <div class="info-box red mt-16"> <h3>Signs of a</h3> <p style="margin-top:8px;">problem • You think about betting even when you\'re not betting</p> <p>• You hide losses from loved ones</p> <p>• You bet with money intended for bills or food</p> <p>• You tried to stop and failed</p> <p>• You gamble to "escape" stress or negative emotions</p> </div> <div class="stat-pills mt-16"> <span class="stat-pill red">3× higher suicidal risk</span> <span class="stat-pill red">Dopamine = cocaine by effect</span> <span class="stat-pill green">CBT works in 60–80%</span> </div>',
            'i.h1.h3': '🚬 Cigarettes — no safe dose',
            'i.h2.h3': '🍺 Alcohol — regular drinking is different from a "cheers"',

            'i.s5.h2': 'What You Gain',
